    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-10-27T22:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-10-27T22:00:00-05:00" n="771"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d771">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.00/10–2848: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Tientsin</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Smyth</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tientsin</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-10-28T11:00:00+08:00"
                            >October 28, 1948—11 a.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received October 28—12:44 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>309. If Embassy approves issuance restrained statements suggested Peiping
                    telegram 594 to Embassy,<note n="26" xml:id="d771fn26">Sent to the Department as
                        telegram No. 396, October 27, 5 p.m., above.</note> we suggest statement be
                    prepared <pb facs="0876" n="866" xml:id="pg_866"/> by Embassy and text sent
                    Tientsin and Peiping for simultaneous release. Such action would preclude
                    possible confusion arising from issuance respective offices of different
                    statements.</p>
                <p>Sent Nanking 552, repeated Department 309.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Smyth</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
